  "texts": [
    "Distributing capability and benefits among different people can lead to a problem if the people do not have a common understanding.",
    "On one hand, providers can create trace links but often do not know the intended use of these particular trace links.",
    "On the other hand, end users do not know how to create trace links, but they know the intended use.",
    "It is a common problem in post-RS traceability, where providers usually are developers, and end users are requirements engineers.",
    "However, the same problem of distributing capabilities and benefits also occurs in pre-RS traceability when many different analysts, requirements engineers, and stakeholders are involved."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}